    "question_id": "Q1",
    "framework": "CAIQ",
    "text": "Are audit and assurance policies, procedures, and standards established, documented, approved, communicated, applied, evaluated, and maintained?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "BNY maintains established, documented, and approved audit and assurance policies, procedures, and standards that are actively communicated, applied, evaluated, and maintained. Management, including the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, with participation by members of the Disclosure Committee, is responsible for ensuring an adequate and effective process for establishing, maintaining, and evaluating disclosure controls and procedures designed to ensure that information required to be disclosed in SEC reports is timely recorded, processed, summarized, and reported, and that such information is accumulated and communicated to management to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosure [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-23-000033::Item_16#0009]. These responsibilities are consistently reflected across reporting periods, reinforcing the ongoing maintenance and evaluation of the control framework [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-22-000043::Item_16#0006]. With respect to external assurance, our Audit Committee has established pre-approval policies and procedures applicable to all services provided by our independent registered public accountants, in accordance with SEC rules, employing both class pre-approval and specific pre-approval approaches for audit and permitted non-audit services [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-25-046216::Item_3#0154]. Together, these governance arrangements demonstrate that audit and assurance standards at BNY are formally established, documented, approved, communicated to relevant stakeholders, applied in practice, periodically evaluated, and maintained.",
